The antient land-mark skreen or bank betwixt the prince or supreame magistrate, and the people of England. By the right of inheritance which the nobility & baronage of England have to sit in the House of Peers in Parliament.
[2], 18 p.
printed by T.W. for Daniel White at the seven Starrs in S. Paul's Church-Yard, London : 1659.
Annotation on Thomason copy: "march. 12th March. 12. 1658"; the 9 in the imprint date has been crossed out. Reproductions of the originals in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery, and the British Librbary.
